Data analysis

Text

fse

We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and nloptwrap optimizer) to predict fse with group and time_point (formula: fse ~ 1 + group + time_point + group * time_point). The model included login_id as random effect (formula: ~1 | login_id). The model’s total explanatory power is substantial (conditional R2 = 0.67) and the part related to the fixed effects alone (marginal R2) is of 0.06. The model’s intercept, corresponding to group = control and time_point = 1st , is at 17.77 (S.E. = 0.52, p < .001, 95% CI [16.75, 18.78]). Within this model:

  • The effect of group [treatment] is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.09, S.E. = 0.73, p = 0.901, 95% CI [-1.34, 1.52]; Std. beta = 0.02, 95% CI [-0.33, 0.37])
  • The effect of time point [2nd] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.59, S.E. = 0.56, p = 0.291, 95% CI [-1.69, 0.50]; Std. beta = -0.15, 95% CI [-0.42, 0.12])
  • The interaction effect of time point [2nd] on group [treatment] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 3.07, S.E. = 0.82, p < .001, 95% CI [1.46, 4.68]; Std. beta = 0.76, 95% CI [0.36, 1.16])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald normal distribution approximation.
